name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Today marks the anniversary of Martin Luther King Jr.'s March on Selma, and with it we reflect on Dr. King's leadership. We remain inspired, and we're looking forward to continuing the fight against hate, prejudice, and racism.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: In 2018, Democrats swept this state and turned NM blue. Since then, we've made progress for New Mexico families, workers, and businesses. Help us continue standing up for New Mexicans by keeping New Mexico blue. Donate $22 today, so we win in 2022.  https://t.co/h9nCpkHnjn

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Thank you, Tirzo, for your support! By making sure every New Mexican has an opportunity to thrive, we're building a state where our future generations are proud to start their careers and grow their families.  https://t.co/UF5xaPYGg8

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Today marks the first day of spring, meaning the start of fiestas, longer hikes into the evenings, and very chaotic weather. It's part of why we love this beautiful state. Happy first day of spring #NM!

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Our northern NM communities reached out about their troubles to obtain propane and we went to work with #SB141. This legislation is going to ensure that on cold nights #NM families have access to propane to heat their homes.  https://t.co/NI2dXkjbm6

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: This #nmleg session we set our eye on FREE college education and we got it done. We passed legislation to guarantee every New Mexican who wants to go to college or a certificate training program can do so – for FREE.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: We became one of the first states to apply to import cheaper prescription drugs from Canada. We took action to lower the cost of lifesaving medicines because New Mexican families should never have to choose between putting food on the table and keeping their families healthy.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Making sure New Mexicans can thrive is about more than tax cuts. That’s why we eliminated copays for behavioral health, capped the price of insulin, and passed the Health Care Affordability Fund, which will help thousands afford health insurance.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: That’s why we’ve taken concrete actions to remedy many of the root causes and contributing factors that lead to pay disparity, such as making higher education free, expanding affordable child care, raising the minimum wage,  and increasing access to affordable health care.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Today on #EqualPayDay we're reminded that women, particularly women of color, make far less than their male counterparts.   Women belong at the table where decisions are made and they deserve equal pay.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: Happy birthday, Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg. You were a champion for women and the right to choose. Today, we remember her as we continue our fight to promote gender equality and access to reproductive health care.

name: Michelle Lujan Grisham
tweet: From day one, this administration has delivered for New Mexicans. That's why we cut taxes for more than half a million New Mexico families last year and we're doing even more to put money back in the pockets of every New Mexican in 2022.
